race.comment: Looks a wide-open affair. REVITUP CHARLIE (9) is a consistent conveyance who has hit the top four in nine of her past ten starts and rarely puts in a poor one. Has placed three of four over this six-furlong journey and should be right there at the business end. MISS ZERMATT (7) has placed two from two over this course and distance and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Finds a nice race and can bounce back. ALFA LILY (6) has a win and a placing from three attempts over this track and trip and rates a genuine top three contender on best form. The well-related COINCIDE (1) (half to 2xG1 winner Converge) is another to get some weight off and may earn a cheque. PRETTY RHO (8) next best from the favourable draw.
